The paper discusses a solution for cross-identification of astronomical databases using a cluster of servers and relational databases. This involves formulating cross-identification problems in a language based on SQL, partitioning queries spatially, and executing them in a parallel framework. This work involves database management, distributed computing, and information retrieval, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.IR, and cs.SI.
